\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any connected domain in space can be chosen as a 
\noun on
control volume
\noun default
 (CV).
 In this document, we denote the control volume as 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 and its boundary, a.k.a.
 the 
\noun on
control surface
\noun default
 (CS), as 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Generally, 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 can move in space.
 We denote the velocity of 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}^{C}$
\end_inset

, in order to distinguish it from the velocity of fluid particles 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}$
\end_inset

.
 According to the relation between 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}^{C}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}$
\end_inset

, we can categorize a CV into three types:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
a 
\noun on
system
\noun default
